node.text:
Presenting the new #GucciAria campaign, envisioned by @alessandro_michele as an exploration of the Ontology of Desire. From the Creative Director’s notes on the campaign: “It’s the birth of Eros, ancient and primigenial force, that drives the desire through the attempt to mend a separation. The myth, in fact, identifies in the relationship with the Other the vital impulse that obliges each of us to restore a lost unity.” Featured in the campaign, shot by @mertalas and @macpiggott, are @maneskinofficial and @kristen_mcmenamy. Creative director #AlessandroMichele, art director #ChristopherSimmonds. #MertandMarcus #Maneskin #TheHackerProject
Music:
‘I WANT YOU’
(Leon Ware, Arthur Ross)
©️ 1974 Almo Music Corp./ Jobete Music Co., Inc.
Licensed by Universal Music Publishing Ricordi Srl.
Artist: Madonna, Massive Attack
℗ 1995 Universal Music Italia Sr

node.text:
In the centenary year of the House, Gucci celebrated its Aria collection through a special fashion show held at the Shanghai Exhibition Centre in China, recreating the set and atmosphere of the #GucciAria film, co-directed by @floriasigismondi and @alessandro_michele, which debuted earlier this year in April. 
#AlessandroMichele
Music:
The soundtrack, by Alessandro Michele and mixed by Lawrence Rothman, comprises a selection of songs 
featuring the word Gucci, speaking to the staying power of the Maison and how profusely it contributed to 
the vocabulary of pop culture.
Lil Pump "Gucci Gang”
(B. Murray / G. Garcia / G. G. Nealy)
Rick Ross feat. Future “Green Gucci Suit”
(R. Ross / A. Stewart / N. Wilburn / D. Hayes)

Bhad Bhabie “Gucci Flip Flops (feat. Lil Yachty)”
(M. McCollum / L. Jae / I. Whitlow / J. Muhammad / L. Porter / D. McCorkell / D. Bregoli / S. Gloade / J. 
Lowe)
Mier “Gucci On My Bag”
Die Antwoord, Dita Von Teese “Gucci Coochie”
(A. Du Toit / W. Jones / J. Nobrega / L. Muggard / Dita Von Teese)
Vitalic, feat. David Shaw “Waiting For The Stars”
(P. Arbez / D. Shaw/ J. Garraud)

node.title: Gucci Aria Fashion Show in Shanghai

node.text:
Named Hortus Deliciarum (Latin for ‘Garden of Delights’), the new #GucciHighJewelry collection draws on the symbolic motifs that are dear to @alessandro_michele and Gucci, taken from the extensive and multifarious canon of House iconography. The saturated, hypnotic hues of a sky at sunset, the romanticism of a rose garden, and motifs from animal kingdom, evoking mythic bestiary and ancient fauna, are 
the ultimate source of inspiration for the new collection, including more than 130 pieces, mainly one of a kind.

node.title: The New Hortus Deliciarum High Jewelry Collection

node.text: The façade of the #GUCCIGAOK flagship store, designed by artist SeungMo Park @HANDLE, is inspired by an imaginary forest. The artist explores the interplay between light and shadow, and the application of wire netting layers results in a vivid symbolism, illustrating the boundaries between what is real and what is an illusion. Reflecting on the environmental issues of our time, the Park expresses the existence and non-existence of nature, his concerns of what can be lost, leaving only the illusion of what might be left. #AlessandroMichele

node.title: Artist SeungMo Park on creating the #GUCCIGAOK façade

node.text: The Beloved Show hosted by #JamesCorden @j_corden finds itself without a musical act and @diane_keaton steps in to save the day with a beautiful rendition of “Am I Blue?” by Harry Akst and Grant Clarke. node.text:
Gucci presents The Beloved Show, hosted by #JamesCorden @j_corden. @dakotajohnson takes the stage with a Dionysus handbag in the new #GucciBeloved campaign—a playful ode to the Hollywood late-night talk show that shines the spotlight on an all-star lineup of celebrities and the House’s signature handbags. 
Directed by artist, photographer and director #HarmonyKorine with creative direction by 
@alessandro_michele and art direction by #ChristopherSimmonds.
Discover more through link in bio. #GucciDionysus #DakotaJohnson #AlessandroMichele

node.title: Dakota Johnson and James Corden on The Beloved Show. #GucciBeloved

node.text:
“In fashion, there has always been this idea of purism. But in reality, fashion has never been pure.” An intimate look behind the scenes of #GucciAria with Creative Director @alessandro_michele. Watch the full backstage interview in our IGTV. Film by Tommaso Bertani @ringfilm. @jaredleto #AlessandroMichele
Music: Gucci Mane ‘Gucci 2 Time’ (G. Mane)

node.title: Behind the Scenes of #GucciAria with Alessandro Michele

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gucci Official on September 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text: Underlining an aesthetic that connects mind and body, in the new #GucciAria campaign, models read works or essays including ‘Three Contributions to the Theory of Sex’ by Sigmund Freud. “Even words are clothes that we decide to wear, after all. Clothes that tie again mind and body in an erotic weaving that connects us to the flesh of the world,” says @alessandro_michele in his notes on the campaign. Discover more through link in bio. #AlessandroMichele

node.text: Known for redefining the conventions of beauty throughout her career, @kristen_mcmenamy appears in an image from the new #GucciAria campaign wearing a multicolor sequin skirt with matching gloves and lace top. Seen in the third image is one of the works featured in the campaign: ‘Simulacra and Simulation’ by Jean Baudrillard. Discover more via link in bio. #AlessandroMichele @alessandro_michele

node.text:
Presenting the new #GucciAria campaign, envisioned by @alessandro_michele as an exploration of the Ontology of Desire. From the Creative Director’s notes on the campaign: “It’s the birth of Eros, ancient and primigenial force, that drives the desire through the attempt to mend a separation. The myth, in fact, identifies in the relationship with the Other the vital impulse that obliges each of us to restore a lost unity.” Featured in the campaign, shot by @mertalas and @macpiggott, are @maneskinofficial and @kristen_mcmenamy. Creative director #AlessandroMichele, art director #ChristopherSimmonds. #MertandMarcus #Maneskin #TheHackerProject
Music:
‘I WANT YOU’
(Leon Ware, Arthur Ross)
©️ 1974 Almo Music Corp./ Jobete Music Co., Inc.
Licensed by Universal Music Publishing Ricordi Srl.
Artist: Madonna, Massive Attack
℗ 1995 Universal Music Italia Sr

node.text: @harrystyles and his band will be wearing a selection of special #Gucci pieces for the entire ‘Love On Tour’ concert series and are captured here on opening night in Las Vegas. #HarryStyles wore a custom Gucci waistcoat embroidered with all-over sequin fringes, wide leg trousers and leather boots.
